    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="324" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30,
                                        1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In discussing with French Government as to evidence in Waller case,
                                what view has been taken by you of use United States could make of
                                the evidence? Have you contended that United States could impugn
                                conclusions of French court although there was evidence supporting
                                the charges, or only if there were entire absence of any such
                                evidence? In either view, inspection of the evidence is needed, of
                                course. But deeming it possible that objection to such inspection
                                may have been made only in the view first named, I ask as to the
                                fact for information and to avoid misapprehension.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
